Structures For building Subsets
2 subsetstr
%% ----------------------------------------------------------------
%% The DataSubSet structure holds a series of integers.  Their main use is
%% to keep track of a subset of objects by their id numbers.
%%     
   DataSubSet 21 dtasubset SystemList
      0  The Highest data point number in the Points
         INT MaximumPoint                       Create
      1  The number of points in the subset
         INT NumberOfPoints                     Create
      2  The Array of integers (ID's) in subset
         INT Points             Pointer         Create Array=NumberOfPoints
      DONE
%% ----------------------------------------------------------------
%% This stores a vector of subsets
   DataSubSetVector 22 dtasubsetvec
      0  The number of data subsets
         INT NumberOfVectors                    Create
      1  The set of datasubsets
         DataSubSet Vector  Create Pointer     Array=NumberOfVectors
      DONE
%% ----------------------------------------------------------------
%% These are two subsets for the classic case of a test and training
%% set of points.
   DataTestBlock    23 dtatestblk
      0  The Build data subset (used for creating structure
         DataSubSet Build   Pointer     Create
      1  The Test data subset (independent set used for testing)
         DataSubSet Test    Pointer     Create
    DONE
DONE

